Terms of Service of Qabel GmbH for the Beta Test Period of Qabel services.

[1] Scope of Application, Formation of Contract

[a] These terms and conditions apply to you as user and us, Qabel GmbH, Goseriede 4, 30159 Hannover (hereinafter referred to as „provider“). In general the version of Terms of Services which is effective by the time the Qabel software was downloaded applies.
[b] Subject of this agreement is the provision of the service "Qabel" (hereinafter referred to as "Qabel service") by the provider. The Qabel service is a telemedia service that enables its users to communicate secure and through End-to-End-Encryption.
[c] By using our services, you agree to the applicability of these Terms of Service and our privacy policy. If you are using our services for a legal entity, you agree to these terms and conditions on behalf of that legal entity.


[2] Use of Qabel Service

[a] During the test period provider supplies the Qabel services to the user free of charge.
To use the Qabel service the client software (currently available for Android Mobile and Windows) (hereinafter referred to as "Qabel client") must be downloaded. The Qabel client may be downloaded from the provider’s website and Google Playstore.
[b] By using Qabel Services, user may be liable to additional telecommunication costs, such as mobile costs and roaming charges.
[c] To register, users must provider their user names, e-mail address and a secure password of their own choice. To complete registration, the user must confirm his/her e-mail address. The user receives a confirmation e-mail from the provider with a confirmation link, which the user has to click within seven days. As long as this registration is not complete, use of the account is restricted to basic functions.
[d] By registering, the user agrees to these terms of service.


[3] Beta Test Period and further Instructions

[a] The Qabel service is currently provided as a beta test only.
Please note that the Qabel software including the Qabel client is an unfinished version of software and it is intended to provide the user with a personal impression of Qabel services. It shall enable the user to test the software’s quality and usability.
[b] The user is aware of the fact that the Qabel service is a beta version. Therefore functionality or freedom of defects can not be guaranteed. As a test version Qabel service and Qabel client may be corrupted and may include   flaws regarding software design, programming and security. Qabel Software must not be used on production systems and such systems that are required for daily use. The software may cause data loss, system crashes, incompatibilities with other software and other incidents. In particular the provider is not obliged to have measures such as data backup or data recovery in place. The user is aware that the Qabel services may change in the future.
[c] Please also note that the encryption system used may be insecure and unreliable in the future.
[d] The beta test period may be terminated or suspended at any time. The user may not claim the Qabel service to being continued. By participating in the beta test the user acquires no right to free or discounted services.
[e] The user may not claim free storage volume in the future.


[4] Data Storage on Test Account – Duties of provider

[a] The user may use Qabel service to save data on his/her personal storage account (Data Hosting). Prior to the upload such data will be encrypted through the Qabel client.
[b] The use of the assigned storage space is solely for test purposes. The proper functioning of the storage space can not be guaranteed.
[c] Storage space may not be used to store non-redundant or otherwise sensitive information. In particular, the provider has no duty of care or storage concerning the data that is transmitted to and saved on the assigned storage space by the user. User alone is responsible for his/her data including any existing legal record retention periods. User is solely responsible to create separate backups prior to uploading data to his/her storage account. Furthermore, before re-installing the Qabel Client user shall make a backup of his/her Qabel identities.
[d] The provider may store the user’s data in a separate data recovery centre.


[5] Duties of the User

[a] The user must not misuse or not to let misuse the Qabel services and must comply with all applicable laws, legal provisions and any other rights of the Federal Republic of Germany. In particular the user agrees not to
store or share any illegal, extremist, violent, racist, pornographic, protection of minors violating content.
store or share any content that violates third party intellectual property rights, copyright or any other rights of third parties.
store or share any defamatory, offensive or fraudulent content.
harass other users, for instance through spam e-mails.
violate the privacy of other users.
store or share or otherwise use malicious software and other software that may affect the integrity and reliability of Qabel services.
[b] Qabel service features the sharing of content with other users. The user is advised to carefully consider with whom he/she shares such content. The user must carefully verify content in particular regarding any third party rights, before sharing it with others and must share content only with persons who trustworthy are personally known to him/her.
[c] To access Qabel services a password is required. The provider strongly recommends to abide by the principles of a safe password assignment. In addition, the user must keep the key, which has been generated by the Qabel service, private and secure from access by any unauthorized third party. In case the user has evidence that his / her account has been compromised or misused by a third party, he/she must inform the provider immediately.
[d] The user is not allowed to relinquish or otherwise assign his/her rights and duties under this agreement.


[6] Fair Use

[a] The provider strives to make the Qabel services available in constant quality and speed. Excessive use of a few users, however, may overburden the capacity of Qabel services as a whole and therefore negatively impact the software performance for the majority of users.
For that reason the provider reserves the right to suspend, restrict or terminate user accounts in case of excessive use of Qabel services (for instance in case of overly high traffic). Please refer to our Fair Use Policy for detailed information.


[7] Intellectual Property

[a] The Qabel service and the software that is used for it are protected by intellectual property rights, including copyright and industrial property rights. As long as the user complies with these Terms of Service, provider grants a restricted, non-transferrable, revocable license, to use the software to access and use the Qabel services.
[b] As long as the software or their single components are offered under an open source licence, we will make that licence available. Provisions of such licence may modify provisions of these terms and conditions.
[c] The user grants the provider the right to the data, which is stored in its data storage, only to such extent necessary to provide the Qabel service according to this agreement.


[8] Cooperation with authorities - Procedures for copyright violations

[a] For prevention and investigation of criminal offenses the provider cooperates with legal authorities as required by applicable laws. It must be emphasised that the provider has no access to encryption keys to decrypt content that has been stored by the user. The provider may block users when it is required by law or judicial or administrative order.
[b] Upon notification of an alleged copyright violation, provider responds to this if the notification complies with the law and DMCA guideline [LINK]. The provider reserves the right to deactivate the account of users that presumably violate copyright or to delete the account of users that repeatedly violate the copyright of third parties.


[9] Liability

[a] Liabilty of provider is determined by German statutory law (Civil Code).
[b] The user must indemnify provider from any third party claims that are based on the data the user has stored on the providers system. This includes compensation for all expenses the provider incurs in connection with the users alleged rights violations. It also includes reasonable expenses for legal actions.
[c] The provider may immediately suspend the test storage accounts when there is reasonable evidence that stored data is unlawful and/or violates the rights of third parties. A reasonable evidence may be assumed if a court, authorities and/or third parties notify the provider of such violations. The provider will notify the user of suspension and its reasons immediately.


[10] Termination

[a] The user may terminate the agreement with the provider at any time by deleting the account by e-mail to delete@qabel.de. The provider reserves ­– because this is a beta test – the right to terminate the contract at any time and without announcement.
[b] Furthermore, the provider reserves the right to terminate the contract based on serious grounds. A serious ground is – inter alia – constituted by a misuse of the Qabel service according to Sec. 5 of the Terms of Service.


[11] Changes of Terms of Services

The provider reserves the right to change these Terms of Service. The user will be informed about changes on the front page of the Qabel client or by e-mail. Changes in favour of the user take effect immediately or, provided that a date of entry into force is determined, on that date. Changes not in favour of the user restricting his/her rights not only insignificantly, take effect at least two weeks after the user has been informed and not deleted his/her account.


