[a] Changes, additions and terminations of contractual agreements must be in writing, as well as the revocation of the requirement for the written form, unless these terms and conditions require the written form themselves.
[b] If any provision of this agreement is held to be invalid or unenforceable, the validity of the remaining provisions will not be affected. The invalid provision shall be replaced by a valid provision that best reflects the commercial purpose of the invalid provision. The same shall apply to omissions.
